                        <p id="fs-idm217118448">
                          A convenient approach for determining
                          <em data-effect="italics">E</em>
                          <sub>a</sub> for a reaction involves the measurement of
                          <em data-effect="italics">k</em> at two or more different temperatures and using an alternate version of the Arrhenius equation that takes the form of a linear equation
                        </p>
